headline: General Motors (GM) Is Up 7.1% After Q3 Delivery Jump and Supply Chain Shift Plans
summary: General Motors recently reported an 8% year-over-year increase in Q3 vehicle deliveries, raised its full-year outlook, and outlined plans to shift supplier sourcing away from China by 2027 to boost supply chain resilience and secure eligibility for U.S. tax credits. GM’s fleet and commercial business saw OnStar subscriptions surge over 50% to 1.6 million, underscoring the growing potential of digital services as a higher-margin revenue stream. headline: What Catalysts Are Changing the Narrative for GM Amid Analyst Optimism and Market Shifts
summary: The Fair Value Price Target for General Motors stock has seen a slight increase, moving from $73.15 to $74.15 per share. This change comes as a wave of analyst optimism follows the company’s robust quarterly performance and improved industry conditions. These factors have prompted upward revisions to price expectations. Stay tuned to learn how you can stay on top of future shifts in the evolving story behind General Motors stock. headline: MagneRide Suspension Revolutionizes Versatility Across All Segments and Power Sources
summary: PARIS, November 26, 2025--As an advanced suspension system, MagneRide stands out for its ability to adapt instantaneously. The fourth generation of MagneRide has redefined and proved its universal applicability across all passenger vehicle segments, from sedans and SUVs to high-performance cars, from gasoline to new energy vehicles.

headline: Tesla struggles to course correct from sales skid
summary: (Reuters) -Tesla CEO Elon Musk has spent much of this year focused on the carmaker’s robotics pursuits and winning shareholder approval for his freshly minted $1 trillion pay package.  In the meantime, the outlook for Tesla's main business – selling cars – is darkening.  The electric-vehicle maker's sales fell 48.5% across Europe in October versus the same month last year, according to data released by the European Automobile Manufacturers' Association on Tuesday. ‌For the year, its sales are down about 30% in the region, while industrywide EV sales jumped 26%.
